        "created_at": "2024-02-25T16:44:55.254Z",
        "cooked": "<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/4X/3/0/f/30f026a7295c27100a2f23e09dc31de8b336a1c5.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/30f026a7295c27100a2f23e09dc31de8b336a1c5\" title=\"desjourneys cork\"><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/4X/3/0/f/30f026a7295c27100a2f23e09dc31de8b336a1c5_2_375x500.jpeg\" alt=\"desjourneys cork\" data-base62-sha1=\"6YVrgd0CDraibrtv8L0u7vmiOu9\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/4X/3/0/f/30f026a7295c27100a2f23e09dc31de8b336a1c5_2_375x500.jpeg, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/4X/3/0/f/30f026a7295c27100a2f23e09dc31de8b336a1c5_2_562x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/4X/3/0/f/30f026a7295c27100a2f23e09dc31de8b336a1c5_2_750x1000.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"75635D\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">desjourneys cork</span><span class=\"informations\">1512\u00d72016 135 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div><br>\nI had this terrific bottle of Desjourneys M\u00e2con-Fuiss\u00e9 bois de la croix last night (after gardening - hence the grubby thumbnail). I\u2019m curious about its aging potential. This cork isn\u2019t DIAM, right? It\u2019s quite waxy and dense - I\u2019m curious if anyone knows what it is, and if it speaks well of laying my last bottles down for a while.</p>",
